[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Pagebanner default.jpg"],["pgname=Hudson"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/cityofhudson.org\/ Hudson"]}]}," is a city in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Columbia County (New York)"],["Columbia County"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["New York (state)"],["New York"]]},".\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Warren Street west view, Hudson, NY.jpg"],["thumb"],["270px"],["Looking west on Warren Street"]]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nHudson is an important city in the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hudson Valley"]]}," that is known for its art galleries, antique shops, and boutiques, and also for blocks upon blocks of beautiful historic buildings. These center on Warren St. but are also present in large numbers on the parallel Columbia St. and some side streets. Hudson is worth at least a detour if not more.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Adirondack-hudson-station.JPG"],["thumb"],["Hudson Train Station"]]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.stewartintlairport.com Stewart International Airport"]}]},", 1180 First St, New Windsor, ",{"type":"''","value":["+1 845"]}," 564-2100."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.albanyairport.com Albany International Airport"]}]},", 737 Albany-Shaker Rd, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Albany (New York)"],["Albany"]]},"."]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.amtrak.com Amtrak"]}]},", 1-800-USA-RAIL. Rail service from Hudson station, 69 South Front St, to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["New York City"]]},"'s Penn Station, as well as north to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Albany (New York)"],["Albany"]]}," or as far as ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Montreal"]]},", Canada."]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\nUS Route 9 is the main road for access to Hudson. State Routes 9G and 23B, which constitute Columbia St. and S. 3rd St. within city limits, are major streets in the center of town. Columbia St. actually forms one end of 7th St. Park, which is the city green. Watch out for traffic along these streets, as they are also truck routes.\n\nA bit south of Hudson, the Rip Van Winkle Bridge traverses the Hudson River and enables access to and from the town of Catskill, on the west side of the river, and the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Catskills"]]},", further afield.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\nThe center of town is walkable. To get further, you will need a vehicle.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:olana_hudson_NY.JPG"],["thumb"],["Olana, home of painter Frederic Church."]]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Olana"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.olana.org"],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone =+1 518 828-0135"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=5720 Route 9G. The mountain-top villa of Frederic Church, one of the most prominent Hudson River painters and one of the United State's most significant artists. From the hilltop home there are sweeping views of the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Catskills"]]},", the Hudson River, and the Taconic Hills. Interior of the house is closed for rehabilitation work through July 2007. Grounds are open year round for walking, hiking, cross-country skiing, and other activities."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Hudson Opera House"],["url=http:\/\/www.hudsonoperahouse.org"],["email="],["address=327 Warren Street"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=New York State's oldest surviving theater, dating from 1855, offers a year round schedule of arts and cultural programming."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Hudson-Athens Lighthouse"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.hudsonathenslighthouse.org"],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Located offshore, limited tours through Hudson Cruises ",{"type":"''","value":["+1 518"]}," 822-1014."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"'''","value":["Fireman Museum"]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"'''","value":["Shaker Museum"]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Hudson-Athens 2006.jpg"],["thumb"],["Hudson-Athens Lighthouse"]]},"\nWalk the length of Warren Street, from the river to the park, admiring the beautifully preserved turn-of-the-century architecture.\n\nSearch for bargains some of the city's dozens of antique shops.\n\nSatisfy your aesthetic eye at the many galleries.\n\nWatch the boats sail up and down the Hudson River from the riverside park.\n\nStop into a Brooklyn-style cafe for a connoisseur's cappuccino.\n\nPick one of the many high-quality restaurants to have a gourmet meal.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\nHudson has a huge number of art galleries and antique stores for a town of its size as well as fashion, fabric, and other craft studios.\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["buy"],["name=Musica"],["url=http:\/\/www.goodmusica.com"],["email="],["address=17 North 4th Street"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone =+1 518 828-1045"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=One of the best community music stores in the country, worth a trip for any amateur ethnomusicologist. Instruments from around the world, sheet music, lessons, advice."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["buy"],["name=The Spotty Dog"],["url=http:\/\/www.thespottydog.com"],["email="],["address=440 Warren Street"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Bookstore\/art supply store with a great selection, doubl